31#include <sys/cdefs.h>
32__KERNEL_RCSID(0, "$NetBSD: dvo_sil164.c,v 1.2 2018/08/27 04:58:23 riastradh Exp $");

34#include "dvo.h"
35
36#define SIL164_VID 0x0001
37#define SIL164_DID 0x0006
38
39#define SIL164_VID_LO 0x00
40#define SIL164_VID_HI 0x01
41#define SIL164_DID_LO 0x02
42#define SIL164_DID_HI 0x03
43#define SIL164_REV 0x04
44#define SIL164_RSVD 0x05
45#define SIL164_FREQ_LO 0x06
46#define SIL164_FREQ_HI 0x07
47
48#define SIL164_REG8 0x08
49#define SIL164_8_VEN (1<<5)
50#define SIL164_8_HEN (1<<4)
51#define SIL164_8_DSEL (1<<3)
52#define SIL164_8_BSEL (1<<2)
53#define SIL164_8_EDGE (1<<1)
54#define SIL164_8_PD (1<<0)
55
56#define SIL164_REG9 0x09
57#define SIL164_9_VLOW (1<<7)
58#define SIL164_9_MSEL_MASK (0x7<<4)
59#define SIL164_9_TSEL (1<<3)
60#define SIL164_9_RSEN (1<<2)
61#define SIL164_9_HTPLG (1<<1)
62#define SIL164_9_MDI (1<<0)
63
64#define SIL164_REGC 0x0c
65
66struct sil164_priv {
67 //I2CDevRec d;
68 bool quiet;
69};
70
71#define SILPTR(d) ((SIL164Ptr)(d->DriverPrivate.ptr))
72
73static bool sil164_readb(struct intel_dvo_device *dvo, int addr, uint8_t *ch)
74{
75 struct sil164_priv *sil = dvo->dev_priv;
76 struct i2c_adapter *adapter = dvo->i2c_bus;
77 u8 out_buf[2];
78 u8 in_buf[2];
79
80 struct i2c_msg msgs[] = {
81 {
82 .addr = dvo->slave_addr,
83 .flags = 0,
84 .len = 1,
85 .buf = out_buf,
86 },
87 {
88 .addr = dvo->slave_addr,
89 .flags = I2C_M_RD,
90 .len = 1,
91 .buf = in_buf,
92 }
93 };
94
95 out_buf[0] = addr;
96 out_buf[1] = 0;
97
98 if (i2c_transfer(adapter, msgs, 2) == 2) {
99 *ch = in_buf[0];
100 return true;
101 }
102
103 if (!sil->quiet) {
104 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("Unable to read register 0x%02x from %s:%02x.\n",
105 addr, adapter->name, dvo->slave_addr);
106 }
107 return false;
108}
109
110static bool sil164_writeb(struct intel_dvo_device *dvo, int addr, uint8_t ch)
111{
112 struct sil164_priv *sil = dvo->dev_priv;
113 struct i2c_adapter *adapter = dvo->i2c_bus;
114 uint8_t out_buf[2];
115 struct i2c_msg msg = {
116 .addr = dvo->slave_addr,
117 .flags = 0,
118 .len = 2,
119 .buf = out_buf,
120 };
121
122 out_buf[0] = addr;
123 out_buf[1] = ch;
124
125 if (i2c_transfer(adapter, &msg, 1) == 1)
126 return true;
127
128 if (!sil->quiet) {
129 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("Unable to write register 0x%02x to %s:%d.\n",
130 addr, adapter->name, dvo->slave_addr);
131 }
132
133 return false;
134}
135
136/* Silicon Image 164 driver for chip on i2c bus */
137static bool sil164_init(struct intel_dvo_device *dvo,
138 struct i2c_adapter *adapter)
139{
140 /* this will detect the SIL164 chip on the specified i2c bus */
141 struct sil164_priv *sil;
142 unsigned char ch;
143
144 sil = kzalloc(sizeof(struct sil164_priv), GFP_KERNEL);
145 if (sil == NULL)
146 return false;
147
148 dvo->i2c_bus = adapter;
149 dvo->dev_priv = sil;
150 sil->quiet = true;
151
152 if (!sil164_readb(dvo, SIL164_VID_LO, &ch))
153 goto out;
154
155 if (ch != (SIL164_VID & 0xff)) {
156 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("sil164 not detected got %d: from %s Slave %d.\n",
157 ch, adapter->name, dvo->slave_addr);
158 goto out;
159 }
160
161 if (!sil164_readb(dvo, SIL164_DID_LO, &ch))
162 goto out;
163
164 if (ch != (SIL164_DID & 0xff)) {
165 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("sil164 not detected got %d: from %s Slave %d.\n",
166 ch, adapter->name, dvo->slave_addr);
167 goto out;
168 }
169 sil->quiet = false;
170
171 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("init sil164 dvo controller successfully!\n");
172 return true;
173
174out:
175 kfree(sil);
176 return false;
177}
178
179static enum drm_connector_status sil164_detect(struct intel_dvo_device *dvo)
180{
181 uint8_t reg9;
182
183 sil164_readb(dvo, SIL164_REG9, &reg9);
184
185 if (reg9 & SIL164_9_HTPLG)
186 return connector_status_connected;
187 else
188 return connector_status_disconnected;
189}
190
191static enum drm_mode_status sil164_mode_valid(struct intel_dvo_device *dvo,
192 struct drm_display_mode *mode)
193{
194 return MODE_OK;
195}

197static void sil164_mode_set(struct intel_dvo_device *dvo,
198 const struct drm_display_mode *mode,
199 const struct drm_display_mode *adjusted_mode)
200{
201 /* As long as the basics are set up, since we don't have clock
202 * dependencies in the mode setup, we can just leave the
203 * registers alone and everything will work fine.
204 */
205 /* recommended programming sequence from doc */
206 /*sil164_writeb(sil, 0x08, 0x30);
207 sil164_writeb(sil, 0x09, 0x00);
208 sil164_writeb(sil, 0x0a, 0x90);
209 sil164_writeb(sil, 0x0c, 0x89);
210 sil164_writeb(sil, 0x08, 0x31);*/
211 /* don't do much */
212 return;
213}
214
215/* set the SIL164 power state */
216static void sil164_dpms(struct intel_dvo_device *dvo, bool enable)
217{
218 int ret;
219 unsigned char ch;
220
221 ret = sil164_readb(dvo, SIL164_REG8, &ch);
222 if (ret == false)
223 return;
224
225 if (enable)
226 ch |= SIL164_8_PD;
227 else
228 ch &= ~SIL164_8_PD;
229
230 sil164_writeb(dvo, SIL164_REG8, ch);
231 return;
232}
233
234static bool sil164_get_hw_state(struct intel_dvo_device *dvo)
235{
236 int ret;
237 unsigned char ch;
238
239 ret = sil164_readb(dvo, SIL164_REG8, &ch);
240 if (ret == false)
241 return false;
242
243 if (ch & SIL164_8_PD)
244 return true;
245 else
246 return false;
247}
248
249static void sil164_dump_regs(struct intel_dvo_device *dvo)
250{
251 uint8_t val;
252
253 sil164_readb(dvo, SIL164_FREQ_LO, &val);
254 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("SIL164_FREQ_LO: 0x%02x\n", val);
255 sil164_readb(dvo, SIL164_FREQ_HI, &val);
256 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("SIL164_FREQ_HI: 0x%02x\n", val);
257 sil164_readb(dvo, SIL164_REG8, &val);
258 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("SIL164_REG8: 0x%02x\n", val);
259 sil164_readb(dvo, SIL164_REG9, &val);
260 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("SIL164_REG9: 0x%02x\n", val);
261 sil164_readb(dvo, SIL164_REGC, &val);
262 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("SIL164_REGC: 0x%02x\n", val);
263}
264
265static void sil164_destroy(struct intel_dvo_device *dvo)
266{
267 struct sil164_priv *sil = dvo->dev_priv;
268
269 if (sil) {
270 kfree(sil);
271 dvo->dev_priv = NULL;
272 }
273}
274
275struct intel_dvo_dev_ops sil164_ops = {
276 .init = sil164_init,
277 .detect = sil164_detect,
278 .mode_valid = sil164_mode_valid,
279 .mode_set = sil164_mode_set,
280 .dpms = sil164_dpms,
281 .get_hw_state = sil164_get_hw_state,
282 .dump_regs = sil164_dump_regs,
283 .destroy = sil164_destroy,
284};
